OakScript
=========

Version 0.05
Copyright (c) Andrew Timmins, 2025.

OakScript is a lightweight, easy-to-read scripting language designed for rapid prototyping, automation,
and educational purposes.

Its syntax is simple and intuitive, making it accessible for both beginners and experienced programmers.

OakScript supports core programming concepts such as variables, arithmetic, strings, booleans,
floating-point numbers, arrays, and buffers.

With clear structure and straight forward commands, OakScript enables users to quickly write script for a variety of tasks,
From basic calculations to more complex logic and data manipulation.


